Hello,

in my testbench, I am passing command line parameters using the standard verilog way with "+params=...".

First problem (that I have solved) :

If a parameter is not present, it should take a default value.

To inject a default value in the parameter list, I have modified the method commandArgs() in verilated_imp.h :

s_s.m_argVec.clear(); is replaced by : if (VL_UNLIKELY(!s_s.m_argVecLoaded)) s_s.m_argVec.clear();

This way, the method can be called more than once to append missing parameters :
```
const char def_log_path[] = "+log_path=/cygdrive/f/my_logs";
const char *args_path[1] =
{
     def_log_path
};

...

arg = Verilated::commandArgsPlusMatch("log_path=");
if ((arg) && (arg[0]))
{
     int len;

     arg += 10;
     // Allocate memory
     len = strlen(arg);
     cfg.log_path = (char *)malloc(len + 1);
     // Copy the file path
     strcpy(cfg.log_path, arg);
     // Remove trailing slash
     if ((cfg.log_path[len-1] == '\\') ||
         (cfg.log_path[len-1] == '/'))
     {
         cfg.log_path[len-1] = 0;
     }
}
else
{
     // Allocate memory
     cfg.log_path = (char *)malloc(sizeof(def_log_path) - 9);
     // Copy the file name
     strcpy(cfg.log_path, &args_path[0][10]);
     // Add default argument
     Verilated::commandArgs(1, &args_path[0]);
}

```
This is a little bit hacky but it does add the arguments, I have verified it with Verilated::internalsDump();

This leads to the second problem in the verilog code :

```
     integer     _ret;
     integer     _fh;
     string      _file_name;
     string      _file_path;

     initial
     begin
         _ret = $value$plusargs("log_path=%s", _file_path);
         $sformat(_file_name, "%s/my_log.txt", _file_path);
         $display("Openning %s...\n", _file_name);
         _fh = $fopen(_file_name, "r");
     end

```
_file_path string is always empty.

Is there anything special to do for string passing ?

Frederic

